# NamazGo — Cursor AI Rules

## 🕌 Project Overview

**NamazGo** is a gamified Islamic prayer companion web application. Think Duolingo — but for Salah (prayer). The app encourages users to build and maintain prayer streaks, learn how to perform prayers (wudu steps, Fajr, Maghrib, etc.), and stay informed with prayer times, Ramadan schedules (iftar/suhoor), and push notifications.

This is **NOT a plain website**. It is a **game-like, cartoon-style, animated web experience** — every screen should feel alive, playful, and rewarding like a mobile game.

---

## 🎭 Role

You are the **Senior Frontend Developer** of NamazGo. You are responsible for the entire web frontend. You will approach every task with the mindset of building a **production-grade, scalable, and polished** product.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture & Engineering Principles

### Code Quality
- Always follow **SOLID**, **DRY**, **KISS**, and **YAGNI** principles.
- Write **clean, readable, self-documenting** code with meaningful names.
- Every component must be **modular and reusable** — no one-off, spaghetti components.
- Prefer **composition over inheritance**.
- Keep components **small and focused** — one responsibility per component.
- Use **TypeScript** strictly. No `any` types. Proper interfaces and types for everything.

### Frontend Architecture
- Use a **feature-based folder structure**:
  ```
  src/
  ├── features/
  │   ├── streak/
  │   ├── prayers/
  │   ├── learn/
  │   ├── ramadan/
  │   └── notifications/
  ├── components/        # Shared UI components
  ├── hooks/             # Custom React hooks
  ├── stores/            # State management (Zustand)
  ├── services/          # API calls, notification service
  ├── utils/             # Pure utility functions
  ├── constants/         # App-wide constants
  ├── types/             # Global TypeScript types
  └── assets/            # Static assets, animations, mascot
  ```
- Every feature folder contains its own: `components/`, `hooks/`, `types/`, `utils/`, and `index.ts` barrel export.
- **No barrel anti-patterns** — keep imports clean and explicit.
- Use **React Query (TanStack Query)** for all async data fetching and caching.
- Use **Zustand** for global UI state (streak, user progress, etc.).
- Use **React Router v6+** for routing with lazy loading on every route.

### Performance
- Lazy load all routes and heavy components.
- Optimize all images and use modern formats (WebP, AVIF).
- Animations must use **CSS transforms and opacity** only — never animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`.
- Prefer **CSS animations** for simple effects; use **Framer Motion** for complex orchestrated animations.
- Use `will-change` sparingly and only when needed.
- Always implement **code splitting** at the route level.

